This paper deals with network interconnectivity and routing, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of centralized control and programmable fabrics, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the potential for security issues, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms for path embedding, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
